main event: A radar operator observed an object enter the radar scope and disappear approximately 3-5 minutes later on 23 July 1956.
interesting points: The observation was made using ground-radar technology,The object was only detected on radar and not visually seen,The observation lasted approximately 3-5 minutes,There is no corroborative data in the file regarding this sighting,The conclusions suggest the object could possibly be a balloon or aircraft.
